{"key":"post-8568317","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8568317</id>\n<content>Stuff it with polyfill and then foil over that.&amp;nbsp; The polyfill prevents contaminants entering as the agar cools.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't put more than 300ml in a 500ml flask or it's going to boil over.&amp;nbsp; To mitigate boilover, use more water in your PC so it cools slower, and rather than shutting off the stove at the end of the cycle, turn it off for a few minutes, and then when the pressure drops a few psi, turn the stove back on to arrest the desent, then turn it off again.&amp;nbsp; Do the above a few times and there won't be any boilover.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;After pouring the dishes and allowing them to cool, I put them back in the sleeves until ready to use.&amp;nbsp; They'll last a month that way, provided they don't get any mold or bacteria on them.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8568387</next>\n<prev>8568259</prev>\n<first>8568259</first>\n<last>8568387</last>\n<when>1214529274</when>\n<utime>06/27/08 04:14 AM</utime>\n</post>"}